# Davos Links / atajo

Build Davos Links as a Cloudflare-native URL shortener for `links.davosdo.dev`.
Keep Davos Links as the technical project name and use `atajo by davosdo` as
the public-facing identity.

## Non-Negotiables

- TanStack Start on Cloudflare Workers.
- Better Auth at `/api/auth/*`.
- D1 binding `DB`.
- KV binding `LINK_CACHE`.
- Workers Analytics Engine binding `ANALYTICS`.
- Dashboard at `/dashboard`.
- Public redirects at `/:shortPath`.

## Runtime Architecture

- D1 is the source of truth for auth, workspaces, domains, links, tags, campaigns, API keys, and daily aggregates.
- KV is a hot redirect cache.
- Analytics Engine receives compact click events from redirect handling.
- Better Auth owns sessions and cookies.
- Cloudflare bindings are server-only.

## Reserved Paths

Reject `dashboard`, `api`, `health`, `assets`, `_build`, `_static`, `favicon.ico`, `robots.txt`, `sitemap.xml`, `login`, `logout`, `register`, `settings`, `admin`, and `app`.

Also reject custom paths starting with `dashboard/`, `api/`, `assets/`, `_build/`, or `_static/`.

## UI Rules

- Use the geometric atajo A mark and lowercase wordmark; show `by davosdo` on spacious surfaces.
- Tripwire-inspired vivid-light, precise developer-tool UI.
- Geist-style sans and mono typography.
- Use only atajo blue and route coral plus warm neutrals. Blue carries primary/current/info/success; coral carries comparison/campaigns/warning/destructive.
- Status must also use text, icons, shapes, or patterns. User-selected tag swatches are the only arbitrary-color exception.
- Compact controls, fine borders, clear hierarchy.
- Use controlled dither on major surfaces; avoid glassmorphism, oversized cards, permanent sparkles, or visual clutter.
